      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 67: `isPluginOverwrite` treats any `Body !\u003d\u003d OriginalBody` as an extension modification. For edited messages, empty/missing `OriginalBody`, or messages whose original body role is not populated, this can incorrectly show the extension indicator and the original-message toggle. Gate this on the model actually providing an original plugin body, or on an explicit daemon role that indicates a plugin overwrite. Example:\\n```suggestion\\nproperty bool isPluginOverwrite: OriginalBody !\u003d\u003d \\\"\\\" \u0026\u0026 Body !\u003d\u003d OriginalBody\\n```\\nIf empty strings are valid original messages, prefer an explicit boolean role instead.",
      "revId": "8820437952e4bbe13e0806b53ee99bf514ee70cc",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
